Reasoning: The paper discusses a computational model inspired by a biological substrate, and utilizes principles of Cellular Automata and Learning Automata. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on modelling and simulating the behaviour of living organisms, cs.NE and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of Cellular Automata also suggests cs.SY as a possible sub-category. The mention of Logic Gates in the title suggests cs.LG as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on solving complex mathematical problems suggests cs.DS as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
